{"at":804558113.079564,"detail":"---\n\n## Product Lead Report — Issue #45: `chunkText` sentence-aware text chunker\n\n### 1. Where the new module goes\n\n**`apps\/web\/src\/lib\/chunk-text.ts`** — colocated with the other shared utility modules:\n\n| File | Purpose |\n|------|---------|\n| `apps\/web\/src\/lib\/language-utils.ts` | Language filter utilities (pure functions) |\n| `apps\/web\/src\/lib\/voice-utils.ts` | Voice helpers (`stripSsml`, `truncateToVariantLimit`) |\n| `apps\/web\/src\/lib\/similar-voices.ts` | Scoring-based voice recommendations |\n| `apps\/web\/src\/lib\/provider-catalog.ts` | Per-provider catalog aggregation |\n| **`apps\/web\/src\/lib\/chunk-text.ts`** | ← **new file** |\n\n**Tests**: **`apps\/web\/src\/lib\/chunk-text.test.ts`** — colocated `.test.ts` pattern used everywhere (`language-utils.test.ts`, `provider-catalog.test.ts`, etc.).\n\n### 2. Existing conventions (from reading real files)\n\n- **Imports**: Colocated modules import each other via `.\/` relative paths (e.g., `'.\/language-utils'`). SvelteKit's `$lib` alias resolves to `src\/lib\/`, so callers elsewhere would import as `'$lib\/chunk-text'`.\n- **File structure**: A JSDoc block at the top describing the module's purpose, then the exported functions, each with its own JSDoc.\n- **TypeScript**: Strict mode, `\"type\": \"module\"` (ESM), `moduleResolution: \"bundler\"`.\n- **Exports**: Named exports only (no `export default` observed in any utility module).\n- **Pure functions**: All utilities are side-effect-free pure functions — `chunkText` fits this perfectly.\n\n### 3. Test framework & patterns\n\n- **Runner**: `vitest` (v4.x) — triggered by `npm run test` → `npm --workspace apps\/web run test` → `vitest run`\n- **Test file pattern**: `src\/**\/*.test.ts` (configured in `vitest.config.ts`)\n- **Style**: `describe`\/`it` blocks, `expect` assertions imported from `'vitest'`. Functions imported directly from the module under test.\n- **Existing example**: `language-utils.test.ts` (373 lines) — comprehensive coverage with fixtures and per-function describes.\n\n### 4. Existing related code (context, no change needed)\n\n- **`apps\/web\/src\/lib\/synthesis\/constraints.ts`** — currently does naive truncation via `input.slice(0, variant.maxInputChars)`. This is where `chunkText` would eventually be wired in (out of scope for this issue).\n- **`apps\/web\/src\/lib\/voice-utils.ts`** — has `truncateToVariantLimit()` which also does naive slice. Another future wiring point.\n- **`VoiceVariant.maxInputChars`** in `types.ts` — the per-variant character limit that callers would pass as `maxLength`.\n\n### 5. Function signature & contract (from the acceptance criteria)\n\n```typescript\nexport function chunkText(text: string, maxLength: number): string[];\n```\n\n**Semantics** (confirmed by reading the issue):\n\n| Input | Output |\n|-------|--------|\n| `\"\"` or whitespace-only | `[]` |\n| Already ≤ `maxLength` | `[text]` (single chunk, unchanged) |\n| Multiple sentences fitting ≤ maxLength | Packed into chunks, breaking at `.`, `!`, `?` + whitespace |\n| Single sentence > maxLength | Hard-split into `maxLength`-sized pieces (no content dropped) |\n| `maxLength <= 0` | Throws an error |\n\n**Invariants**:\n1. No chunk has `length > maxLength`\n2. Concatenating all chunks reproduces the input's non-whitespace content in order\n\n### 6. Build & test verification\n\n- `npm run build:web` — runs `node scripts\/publish-catalog.mjs && npm run -w apps\/web build` (SvelteKit sync + Vite build)\n- `npm run test` — runs `vitest run` in `apps\/web`\n\nBoth must pass green before this is done.\n\n### 7. Out of scope (confirmed)\n\n- No wiring into dispatch\/synthesis path\n- No provider-specific limit lookups\n- No language-specific segmentation beyond `.?!`\n\n---\n\n**Ready for the architect phase.** The module location, conventions, test framework, and acceptance criteria are all clearly defined from a product perspective.","phase":"product","ticketId":"45","outcome":{"note":{}},"id":"45-53"}
